    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect encoding of EPS attach type in NAS messages\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_u8_eps_attach_type()` function was incorrectly constructing a full byte with IEI bits instead of just returning the EPS attach type value. This caused issues when the function's return value was used in NAS message encoding where only the lower 3 bits should be used.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsAttachType.c`: Simplified `encode_u8_eps_attach_type()` to directly return the EPS attach type value (`*epsattachtype & 0x7`) instead of unnecessarily constructing a full byte with IEI bits.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen encoding Attach Request messages, the EPS attach type field was being incorrectly set in the initial registration request message. This could be observed in the encoded NAS PDU where the attach type bits were not correctly positioned, leading to potential interoperability issues with network nodes that strictly validate the attach type field.\n\nThe issue manifested as malformed initial NAS messages during UE registration, where the attach type value was incorrectly encoded due to the function returning more bits than expected by the calling code in `AttachRequest.c`.\n\n"
}